SUMMARY:Punk Software Hack Night: Build Tools That Work for You
LOCATION:San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nSoftware used to be a tool you owned. Now it's 
 mostly something that's done to you: apps that harvest your data\, platfor
 ms that lock you in\, feeds designed to monetize the gap between your inte
 ntions and your attention. Punk software is the alternative. Software that
 's loyal to you. Tools you build\, own\, understand\, and can change.\n\nA
 s Kanjun Qiu\, Imbue CEO\, puts it: “You don’t have to wait for policy
 makers anymore\, because cheap AI coding means you can now choose\, build\
 , and tear down the software in your own life.”\n\nThis hack night is fo
 r anyone who’s unhappy with the way tech and AI is going and wants to do
  something about it. You do not need to be a programmer\; we'll teach you 
 how to use AI tools. Come if you code\, design\, write\, organize\, resear
 ch\, make spreadsheets\, break workflows\, hate your current tools\, or ha
 ve ever thought: there has to be a better way to do this.\n\nBring a lapto
 p\, a charger\, and join the punk software movement.\n\nHow the night work
 s:\n\n5:30pm — Doors open. Come in\, grab food and drinks\, meet people\
 , and settle in.\n\n6:00pm — Kickoff + idea jam. Kanjun will share why w
 e care about punk software and what’s newly possible with AI coding tool
 s\, then we’ll do a short activity to help people meet\, surface problem
 s worth building for\, and choose a direction for the night.\n\n6:20pm —
  Build time. Pick something and make it.\nTechnical? Great.\n\nNon-technic
 al? Also great. We’ll help you get set up with AI coding tools and find 
 a way in.\n\n8:30pm — Optional Show & tell. Work-in-progress demos. Half
 -finished\, janky\, and held together with duct tape is very much the spir
 it of the thing.\n\n—\n\nImbue is an AI company building software that b
 elongs to you. We’re building toward an open agent ecosystem where you c
 an understand\, modify\, and verify AI agents\, so they only work in your 
 interest. Learn about our work and what we stand for: www.imbue.com\n\nCal
 endar: Imbue Events\n\nHosts: Michelle Simonek\, Kanjun Qiu\, Bowei\n\nEve
 nt page: https://luma.com/e494jmrl
URL:https://luma.com/e494jmrl
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
