SUMMARY:Open Tab № 02
LOCATION:San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe tools got easier. The thinking didn't.\n\nM
 eridian's open tab is a short-form talk series where designers share what 
 they're exploring outside of work— a side project\, a craft obsession\, 
 a question they're chewing on\, something with no deliverable attached. De
 cks welcome\, polish optional.\n\nThree speakers. 10 minutes each. Then th
 e room.\n\nJuly's lineup\n\nOmar Mohammad\, design and research at CAMEL 
 • A windmill\, earth mosque(s)\, a minaret\, an airport\, and a village:
  indigenous and vernacular architecture in Afghanistan\n\nEric Howard\, co
 -founder of Direct Message\, Hyperdeck\, and Hard Objects • The Magic Bu
 tton: Design in an era of extreme automation\n\nMichelle Chang\, founder o
 f Seafoam Studio • DaaS (dance as a service)\, Using service design to c
 reate joy through movement\n\nProgram\n- 6:30pm doors open\n- 7:00pm intro
  hellos\n- 7:10pm talks begin\n- 9:30pm hometime or elsewhere\n\nHosted by
  Meridian by Noon\, in San Francisco.\n\nGot an open tab? Come share it. 
 → Apply here ✨\n\nCalendar: Meridian\n\nHosts: Belinda Huang\n\nEvent 
 page: https://luma.com/opentab002
URL:https://luma.com/opentab002
