SUMMARY:The Epic of… Will O'Brien (Ulysses)
LOCATION:San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nWe're kicking off a new monthly series. The con
 cept is simple: we put a founder who's building something straight out of 
 a sci-fi novel on stage\, break down their grand vision\, and let a live c
 rowd decide if it actually holds water.\n\nOur first guest is Will O'Brien
 \, co-founder of Ulysses. They build cheap\, autonomous ocean robots. They
 ’re starting off by restoring seagrass meadows (which trap carbon faster
  than rainforests)\, but the plan is to tackle any part of the ocean econo
 my that still relies on expensive human crews. They’ve already got real 
 revenue\, five generations of vehicles\, and they name their robots after 
 sea monsters. The company is literally called Ulysses\, so the epic brandi
 ng writes itself.\n\nThe format is a live narrative stress-test. We'll spe
 nd 45 minutes with Will unpacking the actual reality of his business: the 
 vision\, the team he's recruiting\, the skeptics he has to convince\, and 
 whatever is most likely to kill the company.\n\nAfter that\, it's on you. 
 The audience gets to grill him with the hardest questions. We take a vote 
 at the start of the night\, and another at the end to see if he actually w
 on you over. That shift in the room is the whole point of the event.\n\nCo
 me hang out if you're a founder\, an engineer who'd rather build physical 
 robots than another chatbot\, someone who invests in hard problems\, or if
  you just want to watch someone defend their life's work in real time.\n\n
 📍 A space in the Mission\, San Francisco (address sent on RSVP) 🗓️
  July 8th\, doors 5:30\, we start 6:00 🎟️ ~60 seats\, curated. Record
 ed and clipped.\n\nAbout the Host:\nSavant is an early-stage fund and ecos
 ystem for exceptional technologists pursuing good quests: hard\, consequen
 tial\, civilization-defining ideas. We help top founders explore & start n
 ew companies in Physical AI through a powerful network of peers\, a dedica
 ted hardware lab\, and founder-led support – often before we ever write 
 a check. Together\, let's move civilization forward!\n\nHosted by Hugo Ams
 ellem (Babylon) and Jeson Lee (Savant).\n\nCalendar: Savant VC\n\nHosts: J
 eson Lee\, Hugo Amsellem\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/sv79uxnf
URL:https://luma.com/sv79uxnf
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
