SUMMARY:Equinox Optimized Volume Four: Strength with Fort
LOCATION:Equinox Sports Club San Francisco\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nOptimized is a series of events at Equinox’s 
 flagship San Francisco Sports Club\, centered on becoming the strongest\, 
 healthiest version of yourself.\n\nVolume 4 focuses on strength: a core pi
 llar of healthy aging\, especially in the peptide era.\n\nFort is a new we
 arable designed to help active people build strength without becoming obse
 ssed with metrics. It tracks strength training\, Pilates\, fitness classes
 \, recovery\, sleep\, steps\, and HRV\, then translates it into simple gui
 dance on consistency\, progress\, and recovery.\n\nMiranda Nover\, Founder
  of Fort\, will join Volume 4 to discuss how Fort is helping bridge the ga
 p between working out and building real strength.\n\nFort will also offer 
 live demos of beta devices\, with the technical team on-site to answer que
 stions about how wearables work and how to get the most out of yours.\n\nA
 ttendees receive:\n\nComplimentary 2-day Equinox gym pass\n\nDiscounts on 
 Fort devices and early access to beta\n\nFree samples from our partners:\n
 Circ Bites- Protein bites made with natural ingredients like peanuts\, cho
 colate chips\, dates\, and oats\n\nBish Bar- Protein bar for hormone and m
 enstrual health\n\nPreme Mix- Premium Prebiotic\, Gut Health drinks\n\nSee
 k Coffee- Mold-Free\, Lab-Tested\, Certified Organic Coffee\n\nPoca- Plant
 -based Coffee sweetener with fiber\n\nONE electrolytes - Clean\, performan
 ce-based Electrolytes\n\nPlease arrive to the 4th floor for check-in.\n\n5
 :00PM arrival and drinks · 5:30PM presentation · 6:00PM reception.\n\nCa
 lendar: Equinox Optimized\n\nHosts: John Butler\, Miranda Nover\n\nVenue: 
 Equinox Sports Club San Francisco\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/3gsl7xcz
URL:https://luma.com/3gsl7xcz
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
