SUMMARY:Figma Field Days: SF Intern Mixer
LOCATION:Figma\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nAt Config 2026\, Figma launched Motion\, Shader
 s\, Generative Plugins\, and Code Layers. Join us at Figma's San Francisco
  headquarters to hear directly from the designers and engineers who built 
 them!\n\nSpeakers will share short talks about the behind-the-scenes proce
 ss and give you a chance to ask your latest questions. Stick around after 
 for small bites\, open mingling\, and a chance to win exclusive Figma plus
 hies!\n\nFeatured Speakers\n\nFifi Law (Motion Designer)\nNoah Finer (Soft
 ware Engineer)\nFern Lukban (Software Engineer)\n\nAgenda\n\n6:00 PM: Door
 s open\n6:00 - 6:30 PM: Light bites\n6:30 PM: Welcome remarks\n6:45 - 8:00
  PM: Lightning talks\n8:00 - 9:00 PM: Open mingling\n\nThis event is open 
 to current interns and students based in the Bay Area. A verified Figma fo
 r Education email is required to register. Visit https://www.figma.com/edu
 cation/apply to verify your email.\n\nCapacity is limited to 100 attendees
 . RSVPs will be reviewed and selected based on the quality of responses\, 
 so take a moment to share a little about your background!\n\nWhat is Figma
  for Edu?\n\nFigma for Education is the team at Figma that empowers educat
 ors and students to make the most out of Figma’s tools. Through the Figm
 a for Education program\, qualifying educators and students can access Fig
 ma’s professional tools for free. The Edu team also ensures that our edu
 cation audience has the skills\, inspiration\, and community they need to 
 create at their best.\n\nWhat is Design Meetup?\n\nYour role as a product\
 , brand\, and visual designer is changing with next-gen tools. Design Meet
 up is a place for designers who want to continuously upskill while making 
 meaningful friendships\, bringing together the world’s most ambitious de
 signers. Through in-person events\, virtual workshops\, and an active slac
 k community\, we are your space to learn and define where design is headin
 g.\n\nPhotography and Filming\n\nPlease be aware that this event will be p
 hotographed and filmed. Figma reserves the right to use these images and v
 ideos for marketing and communications purposes. By attending\, you consen
 t to the use of your likeness for these purposes.\n\nSafety and Inclusivit
 y\n\nAll Figma events are inclusive and welcoming of all genders\, sexuali
 ties\, races\, and abilities. Discrimination of any kind will not be toler
 ated. This event is governed by the Figma Code of Conduct.\n\nCalendar: Fi
 gma for Education\n\nHosts: Figma Team\n\nVenue: Figma\n\nEvent page: http
 s://luma.com/2cgvxnz7
URL:https://luma.com/2cgvxnz7
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
