SUMMARY:Future of Us: Dogpatch Block Party!
LOCATION:Pier 70\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nFood\, music\, neighbors\, and a whole lot of c
 halk! This is a day to celebrate the Dogpatch — and to imagine the futur
 e of all of our neighborhoods.\n\nMake new friends\, explore interactive s
 tations\, and add your vision to our chalk art gallery. \n\n⚡ This event
  is part of our Neighborhood Futures day. Check out the programming happen
 ing at The Pearl just a 10 minute walk away\, and if you're a local to the
  neighborhood\, sign up to earn your patches at the first annual Patchwork
  neighborhood crawl! ⚡\n\nDisclaimer: Permits filed and pending.\n\nAbou
 t the Event:\n\nThe Future of Us is marking the generational milestone of 
 the US's 250th anniversary by coming together to celebrate community visio
 ns\, creative expression\, and civic voice.\n\nWe can't celebrate "Neighbo
 rhood Futures" without celebrating our home neighborhood! This community b
 lock party is inspired by our mission to bring our local neighborhood toge
 ther in creative ways. We're partnering with the Dogpatch Arts & Business 
 Association and Pier 70's Building 12 to bring the community a day of musi
 c\, art\, craft\, food\, and beer!\n\nWhat to Expect: \n\nCreative Activat
 ions\n\nChalk Art Gallery: 12+ artists are doing a takeover of our street\
 , filling it with visions of what their dream neighborhoods would be! Don'
 t worry\, we're holding some spots for you to add your own.\n\nDogpatch Ph
 oto Booth: Get your official Dogpatch portrait\, props optional\, but alwa
 ys encouraged.\n\nMeet You Neighbors Lounge: Hang out at one of the lounge
 s set-up with conversation prompts and interactions to make it a little ea
 sier to spark a connection.\n\nBuilding 12 Pop-Ups: Check out the pop-up a
 rt gallery\, artisans\, and special events nearby inside Building 12.\n\nF
 ood\, Drinks & Entertainment\n\nFood Trucks: Expect Bay-wide and local fav
 orite food trucks\, and a few surprise treats.\n\nGreat Beer & Views: Enjo
 y a drink at Standard Deviant next door\, with amazing views of the Bay. I
 f you get there early\, they'll probably have World Cup on!\n\nLive Music:
  We'll have music throughout the evening to keep you moving.\n\nNeighborho
 od Activations\n\nPop by some of the other festival events happening at th
 e same time on-site and nearby:\n\n"Patchwork": A Neighborhood Crawl: For 
 the people who live and work in the neighborhood\, make sure to check out 
 the first ever Patchwork neighborhood crawl. Earn free "patches" and a tot
 e by getting to know your neighborhood! Register here - event starts at 2p
 m!\n\n"Neighborhood Futures" Event: The festival's signature programming i
 s happening a 10 minute walk away at The Pearl. Check out 100+ original ar
 tworks\, conversations from local civic builders and leaders on building c
 ommunity and making an impact in your neighborhood\, and enjoy a live DJ o
 n the roof.  Register here.\n\n"Sardine Games": From 4-6\, head over to an
  immersive\, game-based experience inspired by the Bay's sardine fishery. 
 Register here.\n\nPlanning Your Trip:\n\nParking & Transportation\nStreet 
 parking is available but limited. We recommend rideshare or public transpo
 rtation. The Block Party is easy to reach by the Third Street Muni and a s
 hort walk from the T-Third line.\n\nAccessibility & Considerations\nThis i
 s a largely outdoor event\, with access to Building 12. If you have specif
 ic accommodation questions or requests\, please reach out to future@theple
 nary.co to discuss what's possible.\n\n⚡ About the Future of Us Festival
 \n\nLaunching on America's 250th anniversary\, the inaugural Future of Us 
 festival is a 10-day celebration of civic imagination and possibility. We'
 re turning community-sourced\, expert-crafted visions of the future into a
 rt\, storytelling\, and participatory experiences. Curated by a coalition 
 of artists\, scientists\, storytellers\, and civic builders\, the festival
  features 100+ events spanning every corner of the city (floral labyrinths
 \, speculative future worlds\, dance parties with a purpose\, and neighbor
 hood meet-ups)\, it's a living exploration of what a more creative and gen
 erative civic culture could feel like. Organized around four themes (Green
  Futures\, Social Futures\, Science & Tech Futures\, and Media Futures)\, 
 Future of Us is breaking down the barriers between art\, ideas\, and each 
 other\, and everyone is invited to co-imagine what comes next.\n\n⚡ Lear
 n More: future-of-us.com\n⚡ Check out the Schedule of Events: future-of-
 us.com\n⚡ Follow Us: https://www.instagram.com/futures.us\n\nAbout the O
 rganization\n\nFuture of Us is stewarded by The Plenary\, Co.\, a 501(c)3 
 civic arts and sciences nonprofit based in Dogpatch\, and co-led by a coal
 ition of partners. All donations are tax-deductible. Make a donation here.
 \n\nCalendar: Future of Us\n\nHosts: The Plenary\, Co.\, Nothin But Hits\n
 \nVenue: Pier 70\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/future-of-us-block-party
URL:https://luma.com/future-of-us-block-party
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
