SUMMARY:From Seaweed to Shirt: The Chalk Up Tee Launch + Innovation Lab Tou
 r
LOCATION:The Gate 510\, San Leandro\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nHi everyone!\n\nWe're excited to invite you to 
 Supercarb's first-ever product launch.\n\nSupercarb is a material technolo
 gy company transforming seaweed and agricultural waste into high-performan
 ce textile fibers. Our journey began in a garage in Emeryville\, Californi
 a\, where we invented a new seaweed-based fiber platform. That breakthroug
 h was later recognized and supported by Activate\, a Berkeley-based nonpro
 fit that empowers scientists and entrepreneurs tackling climate change and
  other global challenges.\n\nToday\, we're taking the next step in that jo
 urney.\n\nJoin us as we launch the Chalk Up Tee\, our first product built 
 using Supercarb's Seaweed Tech™\, designed for the climbing and outdoor 
 community.\n\nAgenda\n\nMeet the Team + Brand Launch\n\nThe story behind S
 upercarb\n\nThe vision for the future of textiles\n\nIntroduction to the C
 halk Up Tee\n\nProduct Reveal + Drinks\n\nFirst look at the product\n\nMee
 t fellow climbers\, creators\, and supporters\n\nTry It On + Purchase\n\nE
 xperience the product firsthand\n\nLimited launch-day purchasing opportuni
 ty\n\nInnovation Lab Tour\n\nA behind-the-scenes look at how we turn seawe
 ed into textile fibers using physics\, chemistry\, and a lot of persistenc
 e\n\nWe're incredibly proud of the work that has gone into bringing this p
 roduct to life\, and we'd love for you to celebrate this milestone with us
 .\n\nP.S. Our lab is located inside a historic former Dodge manufacturing 
 facility\, making for a uniquely industrial backdrop to an evening of scie
 nce\, textiles\, and community.\n\nCheers\,\n\nTeam Supercarb\n\nCalendar:
  Personal\n\nHosts: Hitesh Manglani\, Makena Klatt\n\nVenue: The Gate 510\
 n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/zl5j4dij
URL:https://luma.com/zl5j4dij
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
