SUMMARY:Show & Tell: AI for GTM @Notion with Baseten\, Cognition and Samsar
 a
LOCATION:Notion HQ\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nWe've all been to the AI events. The panels. Th
 e hot takes. The "we're exploring AI" platitudes. Everyone's talking — a
 lmost nobody is showing.\n\nThis is the opposite of that.\n\nShow & Tell: 
 AI for GTM is a demo-only event for go-to-market teams actually building w
 ith AI. No slides. No pitches. No thought leadership. Just practitioners o
 pening up their laptops and walking you through the workflows they've buil
 t — the ones they use at work\, every day.\n\nWe're bringing together 5
 –6 GTM operators and engineers who will each demo a real AI-powered work
 flow live: how they set it up\, why they built it\, what it actually does\
 , and what they'd do differently. Expect to see real tools\, real data flo
 ws\, and real results — not a product pitch dressed up as a case study.\
 n\nSubmit a proposal: https://forms.gle/JG9xdhVR3B2x4Vg47\n\nSpeakers from
 :\n\nCognition (David Morse)\n\nBaseten (Ben Levitt)\n\nSamsara (David Ben
 ac)\n\nNotion (TBD)\n\nWant to demo? Apply through the registration form. 
 We're looking for GTM engineers\, RevOps builders\, SDR/AE operators\, and
  marketing technologists who have built something real with AI and are wil
 ling to show their work.\n\nWant to watch? Come ready to steal ideas. This
  is the most tactical AI event you'll attend this year.\n\nCheck out our t
 alks from past events.\n\nUpside is the AI-native data layer for GTM. We e
 xtract raw source signals from everywhere they exist across all systems an
 d transform them into a knowledge graph and make that data available in al
 l the places and ways you need: MCP with cutting-edge tools\, analytics da
 shboards and  hosted interactive miniapps with live data.\n\nCalendar: Ups
 ide\n\nHosts: Mada Seghete\, Dan Ahmadi\, Notion\n\nVenue: Notion HQ\n\nEv
 ent page: https://luma.com/b8ie1m1s
URL:https://luma.com/b8ie1m1s
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
