SUMMARY:AI Philosophy Nights: Indifferent Intelligence
LOCATION:San Francisco\, California
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin us for the next edition of our monthly AI 
 Philosophy Nights where we attempt communal sense-making.\n\nEach month\, 
 we bring together philosophers\, historians\, technologists\, and social s
 cientists for a high-level fireside chat\, followed by small-group salon s
 tyle discussions.\n\nThis session: Giving a Damn in the Age of Indifferent
  Intelligence\n\nThe problem with artificial intelligence\, as our guest p
 uts it\, is that computers don't give a damn. Machines can now write\, con
 verse\, and optimize but they cannot care. And as AI systems take over mor
 e of our work and cater ever more precisely to our preferences\, the deepe
 r risk is the slow erosion of our capacity to care\, to commit\, and to fi
 nd things worth wanting in the first place.\n\nIn this session\, our found
 er Banu Kellner sits down with B. Scot Rousse to explore what care actuall
 y is\, why it may be the missing foundation of the AI alignment problem\, 
 and how we might design technologies to recover our ability to give a damn
 .\n\n6:30-7:00pm Doors Open. Drinks & light bites will be served. Doors wi
 ll be closed at 7pm.\n\n7:00-8:00pm Fireside Chat. Banu & B. will examine 
 care in the age of AI.\n\n8:00-9:00pm Small Group Discussions. Break into 
 small-group conversations to grapple with these questions together.\n\n9:0
 0-9:30pm Whole Group Conversation. We will come back together to share ins
 ights and further questions.\n\n~~~\n\nB. Scot Rousse ("B") Visiting schol
 ar and lecturer in the Philosophy department Uc Berkeley\, and an affiliat
 e researcher at Topos Institute. His work foregrounds the embodied\, skill
 ful\, and caring dimensions of human life often obscured by computational 
 models of mind and intelligence. He has also been drumming in punk bands h
 is entire life. He writes about philosophy and AI at withoutwhy.substack.c
 om\n\nBanu Kellner is an executive coach to AI Founders building frontier 
 technologies. She is the author of the Superhumanist Manifesto and the fou
 nder of the SuperHuman Society\, an organization focused on championing a 
 future where technology expands human dignity\, capability\, and connectio
 n.\n\nSponsored by Imbue. An AI company building tools to empower humans i
 n the AI age. We’re building toward an open agent ecosystem where you c
 an understand\, modify\, and verify AI agents\, so they only work in your 
 interest. Learn about our work and what we stand for: www.imbue.com\n\nCal
 endar: SuperHuman Society \n\nHosts: Banu Kellner\n\nEvent page: https://l
 uma.com/4esilsg5
URL:https://luma.com/4esilsg5
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
