SUMMARY:Fonzi's July Tech Talks
LOCATION:San Francisco\, California
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin us for the July edition of the San Francis
 co AI Engineers Tech Talk\, a gathering focused exclusively on AI engineer
 ing. Whether you’re a seasoned machine learning engineer or a fullstack 
 dev curious about how to work with LLMs\, this is your space to dive deep 
 into real-world projects\, technical challenges\, and creative solutions.\
 n\nWhat to Expect:\nEach month\, we invite AI engineers to share something
  they’ve built\, the challenges they faced\, and how they solved them. I
 t’s all substance\, no fluff\, designed for engineers by engineers.\n\nT
 his Month’s Presenters:\n\nDelphi\nBuilding AI Clones That Scale Human E
 xpertise\nDelphi will share how they are building AI clones that capture e
 xpert knowledge and deliver personalized interactions at scale. The talk w
 ill cover creating reliable knowledge retrieval systems\, improving conver
 sational quality\, scaling expertise through AI assistants\, and the pract
 ical challenges of deploying personalized AI experiences in production.\n\
 nAlex AI\nBuilding AI Recruiters for Faster\, Smarter Hiring\nHiring at sc
 ale requires more than automation\, it requires better candidate evaluatio
 n and a consistent recruiting process. Alex will share how they're buildin
 g AI recruiters that conduct interviews\, streamline hiring workflows\, an
 d help teams identify top talent faster. The session will cover AI-powered
  screening\, live interviews\, workflow automation\, structured candidate 
 evaluation\, and integrating AI into modern recruiting teams.\n\nDeepVerif
 ied\nBuilding Reliable AI Systems with Evaluation Frameworks: Reliable AI 
 systems require continuous evaluation\, not just better models. DeepVerifi
 ed will share how they're building an evaluation framework to measure accu
 racy\, track latency\, monitor historical performance\, and identify trend
 s over time\, helping teams improve RAG and agent workflows with confidenc
 e.\n\nThe Crowd:\nYou’ll be joining a mix of software developers\, data 
 scientists\, AI engineers\, and technical founders working at or curious a
 bout the future of applying AI at the application layer. It’s a casual\,
  high-signal environment perfect for learning something new and meeting pe
 ers in the SF AI Engineering scene.\n\nAgenda:\n\n6:00 to 6:45 PM – Netw
 orking with pizza\, beer\, & wine courtesy of Fonzi AI\n\n6:45 to 6:50 PM 
 – Opening remarks\n\n6:50 to 7:35 PM – Three 10 minutes Tech Talks wit
 h 5 minute Q&A\n\n7:35 to 8:00 PM – Meet the speakers and connect with o
 ther attendees\n\nAbout the host: \nFonzi  is a recruiting platform focuse
 d exclusively on product and AI engineering hires in NYC and SF. We work w
 ith 75+ open roles across the best startups in the city.\n\nHiring?\nWant 
 intros to startups?\n\nCalendar: AI Engineers - SF\n\nHosts: Lauren Cotta\
 n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/jrs8v2ms
URL:https://luma.com/jrs8v2ms
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
