DTSTAMP:20260706T023641Z
DTSTART:20260716T010000Z
DTEND:20260716T030000Z
SUMMARY:ITCH - Businesses share what needs to be built
LOCATION:European Startup Embassy\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\n"The way to get startup ideas is not to try to 
 think of startup ideas. It's to look for problems\, preferably problems yo
 u have yourself."  Paul Graham\n\nMost people who want to build something 
 sit in a room and brainstorm ideas. That is the wrong starting point.\n\nT
 he right starting point is a real problem. Felt by a real person. That is 
 the ITCH worth scratching.\n\nIf you do not have that problem yourself\, c
 ome find it here.\n\nWe ran this once. The room was full\, people left wit
 h ideas to work on\, and kept asking when the next one would be.\n\nHere i
 t is.\n\n​ITCH is a panel discussion with business owners in the SF comm
 unity. We dig into what is actually hard in their business right now. We a
 sk the questions\, you ask the questions\, we go deep. Together\, we find 
 the ITCH.\n\nYou leave with a list of real problems you can actually work 
 on. And some of the panelists might let you pilot your solution with them 
 directly.\n\nNo pitch decks. No imaginary users. Just problems that exist 
 today and people who need them solved.\n\nOh\, and we are bringing some sn
 acks and food.\n\nThis is for anyone who wants to build something. A start
 up\, a side project\, or just something for your CV. Up to you.\n\nCome an
 d leave with an ITCH.\nJuly 15\n\nCalendar: ITCH\n\nHosts: Adam Svec\, Eur
 opean Startup Embassy\, Devinder Sodhi\, Sahar Mor (Bond AI)\n\nVenue: Eur
 opean Startup Embassy\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/zwmgi7l9
