SUMMARY:ElevenLabs x Sauna Hack Night
LOCATION:1185 Mason St\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nElevenLabs x Sauna Startup Hack Night \n\nWhat 
 happens when AI gets a memory and a voice?\n\nOn July 16\, we’re bringin
 g ElevenLabs and Sauna together at the Wordware office in San Francisco fo
 r a startup-focused Hack Night built around voice\, agents\, automation\, 
 and AI-native workflows.\n\nSauna is building an AI that learns how your t
 eam works\, remembers what matters\, and keeps work moving forward.\n\nEle
 venLabs is building agents that can listen\, speak\, type\, and take actio
 n with natural voices and real-time conversation.\n\nOne gives AI memory a
 nd context. The other gives it a voice.\n\nThis night is about what happen
 s when you put those together.\n\nWe’ll start with demos from both teams
 \, then open the room for a focused 90-minute build sprint. Bring an idea\
 , find collaborators\, and build something real. The strongest projects wi
 ll demo live at the end of the night.\n\nWhen: Thursday\, July 16\, 2026 |
  5:30 PM - 9:20 PM PT\nWhere: Wordware office\, 1185B Old Mason Street\, S
 an Francisco\, CA 94129\n\nFormat\n\n5:30 PM — Doors\, food\, and networ
 king\n\n6:00 PM — ElevenLabs and Sauna demos\n\n6:45 PM — 90-minute bu
 ild sprint\n\n8:35 PM — Final demos\n\n9:00 PM — Awards and closing\n\
 nWhat To Bring\n\nYour laptop\n\nAn idea\, or just the willingness to find
  one in the room\n\nThe energy to build something quickly\n\nFood will be 
 provided.\n\nSpace is limited.\n\nCalendar: [SF] Builders Collective\n\nHo
 sts: Sauna\, ElevenLabs\, Adam Chan\, Jonathan Chang\, Tarun Odedra\n\nVen
 ue: 1185 Mason St\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/elevenlabs-sauna-jul16
URL:https://luma.com/elevenlabs-sauna-jul16
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
