SUMMARY:DeepLearning.AI Voice AI Hackathon: The Complete Trip\, powered by 
 Sabre and Vocal Bridge
LOCATION:Mountain View\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nEvery AI agent can act. Few of them can speak.\
 n\nBooking travel is one of the most manual and disconnected experiences i
 n the world. With Sabre's travel APIs and Vocal Bridge's voice layer\, it 
 can be as simple as one conversation.\n\nA real trip isn't built with one 
 booking. There's the flight\, the hotel\, rideshares\, dinner reservations
 \, concert tickets\, and the five confirmation emails you'll never find ag
 ain. Every leg lives in a different app. None of them talk to each other.\
 n\nYour job: make them talk. Prove that flights\, stays\, ground transport
 \, dining\, and other experiences can be pulled into a single conversation
 \, a single itinerary\, all booked and managed by voice AI.\n\nApplication
  only. In-person. Walk-ins will not be admitted.\n\n💻 What you are buil
 ding\n\nBring your rawest idea and build something real - not a chatbot\, 
 not a notification\, but a voice agent that shows up when it matters most.
  Think of the agent that speaks fluent Japanese and English to unscramble 
 a hotel snafu in Osaka after landing at 2am. Or the agent that literally c
 alls the airline on your behalf\, waits on hold so you do not have to\, an
 d speaks to a human agent to rebook your cancelled flight - because some s
 ystems still only work over the phone.\n\nYour submission must use Sabre A
 PIs and Vocal Bridge to qualify for prizes.\n\nTeams of up to 4. Come with
  a team or come solo -  find teammates on Discord or on the day. Each par
 ticipant must register individually.\n\n🗣️ Speakers & Judges\n\nAndre
 w Ng\, Founder at DeepLearning.AI\, General Partner at AI Fund\n\nScott J
 ohnston\, Former CEO of Docker\, Venture Advisor at AI Fund\n\nEli Chen\, 
 Technology Partner at AI Fund\n\nGarry Wiseman\, President of Product and 
 Engineering at Sabre\n\nDan Maloney\, CEO at LandingAI\n\nAshwyn Sharma\, 
 CEO and co-founder of Vocal Bridge\n\n& more judges from Sabre\, American 
 Airlines\, PayPal\, LandingAI\, AI Fund and the broader AI community\n\n
 🎯: Live demos are the Vocal Bridge way\, however they come out.\n\n🏆
 : $5000 in cash prizes\, awards in multiple categories\, product credits a
 nd more.\n\n🥇 : $2500\n\n🥈 : $1500\n\n🥉 : $1000\n\n📅 Agenda\n\
 n8:00 AM : Doors open and check in\n\n9:00 AM : Kickoff\n\n10:00 AM : Hack
 ing begins\n\n4:00 PM: Fireside chats\, Final pitches and Awards\n\n6:30 P
 M: Done 👋\n\n☕: Breakfast\, lunch\, snacks\, and coffee all day.\n\nH
 osts\n\nDeepLearning.AI is the world's leading AI education platform.\n\nS
 abre powers travel for the world's leading airlines\, agencies\, and booki
 ng platforms.\n\nVocal Bridge gives voice to your agents and apps in minut
 es.\n\nPartners\n\nAI Fund co-founds AI companies at the frontier.\n\nAmer
 ican Airlines is one of the world's largest airlines.\n\nPayPal is a leadi
 ng global payment platform.\n\nCalendar: Vocal Bridge Events\n\nHosts: Dee
 pLearning.AI\, Sabre\, Vocal Bridge\, Aditi Dhar\, Ashwyn Sharma\, Jitesh 
 Gupta\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/fmypremp
URL:https://luma.com/fmypremp
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
