SUMMARY:Dwarkesh Unplugged\, presented by WorkOS
LOCATION:SFJAZZ\, San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin us for a special evening with Dwarkesh Pat
 el\, host of  the Dwarkesh Podcast\, in conversation with Dr. Fei-Fei Li\,
  co-founder and CEO of World Labs\, exploring the forces shaping technolog
 y and AI—and what they mean for the future.\n\nWorkOS Founder Michael Gr
 inich will also turn the tables on Dwarkesh\, and sit down with him for a 
 conversation on how he got his start and the story behind building one of 
 the most compelling podcasts in tech.\n\nJuly 22 · SFJAZZ · San Francisc
 o\n\nSpace is limited\; apply now to reserve a seat.\n\nSpeaker Lineup\n\n
 About WorkOS\n\nWorkOS is the infrastructure B2B and AI-native companies u
 se to sell to enterprise. It covers everything enterprise security require
 s: SSO\, SCIM\, RBAC\, Audit Logs\, AI governance\, and more. Engineering 
 teams ship it in days. Trusted by 2\,000+ fast-growing companies\, includi
 ng OpenAI\, Anthropic\, Cursor\, and Vercel.\n\nWorkOS Event Terms & Condi
 tions apply.\n\nCalendar: WorkOS Events\n\nHosts: WorkOS\, Michael Grinich
 \n\nVenue: SFJAZZ\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/f28a739d
