SUMMARY:Scaling revenue at Stripe and Vercel with Jeanne DeWitt Grosser (CO
 O\, Vercel)
LOCATION:San Francisco\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nBaseten is proud to present Heavyweights\, a se
 ries of talks where AI founders learn from the greats.\n\nFew people have 
 navigated how to scale revenue quite like Jeanne DeWitt Grosser.\n\nAs one
  of Stripe's earliest revenue leaders\, she helped build the go-to-market 
 motion that turned a developer tool into the payments infrastructure of th
 e internet. Now as COO at Vercel\, she’s scaling a platform that's becom
 e the default deployment layer for modern web development.\n\nDannie Herzb
 erg\, President at Baseten\, will sit down with Jeanne for a candid conver
 sation on what it takes to scale revenue at an ai-native company like Verc
 el.\n\nSchedule\n\n6:00–7:00 PM — Welcome drinks & snacks\n7 PM — Di
 scussion\n\nThis event is hosted by Baseten — the inference platform beh
 ind some of the most demanding AI workloads in production like\, Abridge\,
  Cursor\, Notion\, and OpenEvidence. Most bring their own models. We make 
 them fast.\n\nCalendar: Baseten Events\n\nHosts: Baseten\n\nEvent page: ht
